items.name: Tetsuya Nomura (Kingdom Hearts / Final Fantasy) Style LoRA
items.description:
Tetsuya Nomura style LoRA

Making models can be expensive. Do you like what I do? Consider supporting me on Patreon üÖøÔ∏è or feel free to buy me a coffee ‚òï

I initially made this one only to further improve my Aqua (KH) pics, it turned out great. It can mimic Nomura's style incredibly well and has even picked up some characters (I managed to do Cloud and Tifa easily, without TI or other description besides 1boy / 1girl and their names).

Triggers with nomura tetsuya but it will pick up the style regardless of the trigger word. Example pics have been made on AnythingElse and AnyLoRA. I suggest weight 1 for the offset version (0.6 for the old one). Last 2 pics are also using my Aqua LoRA.

How to use LoRA's in auto1111:

  • Update webui (use git pull like here or redownload it)

  • Copy the file to stable-diffusion-webui/models/lora

  • Select your LoRA like in this video

  • Make sure to change the weight (by default it's :1 which is usually too high)

items.name: Wilnas (Granblue fantasy)
items.description:
LoRA trained on the humanoid form of the Vermilion dragon, Wilnas, from Granblue Fantasy.

It was trained on Anything V3 (13 images, 10 repeats, 5 epochs), but I find that it produces great result with AbyssOrangeMix2. (Sampling method: Euler a, Steps: 40, CFG 11, LoRA weight: 1)

When using with models that are strong on female generation (such as AOM2), it is recommended that the keyword muscular male is specified in the prompt, otherwise it might produce a genderbent version of him.

Trigger word: wilnas, granblue fantasy, muscular male

Additional keywords that go well with the character's theme: flaming sword, explosion, male focus, fire, fiery wings, fiery hair, flame, pyrokinesis, breathing fire

Additional keywords that makes him hotter: bara, big bulge, large pectorals, pectoral cleavage, sidepec, abs, thighs, bulky

items.name: RatnikaMetaMixV2
items.description:
General use model for realistic anime style.

Variation of RatnikaMix mixed from Anything V4 instead of V3 and F222 instead of F111, and Bstaberpro53robo instead of bstaber.

Realistic anime-style, good for creative clothing and NSFW content.

Recommended Prompt:

masterpiece, highres, intricate, high quality, Detailed face and eyes, best quality

Negative prompt:
extra digits, extra digit, fewer digits, cropped, worst quality, low quality, normal quality, jpeg artifacts, signature, watermark, username, deformed, bad anatomy, mutation, ugly, broken leg, fat, extra legs, extra ears,

Link to VAE used for previews: https://huggingface.co/hakurei/waifu-diffusion-v1-4/blob/main/vae/kl-f8-anime2.ckpt

It is recommended to always gen at resolutions below 512px (preview images were generated at 256x512). Use the hires fix to upscale it to something greater (I used denoise strength 0.5). Preview images has been upscaled by 3.5x (4x for the full nude). Turn off "Restore Faces". Experiment with clipskip 1-2.

My startup arguments for genning at high resolution with higher speeds:
set COMMANDLINE_ARGS= --autolaunch --xformers --opt-split-attention --medvram

I recommend getting an upscaler like 4x_BS_DevianceMIP_82000_G, 4x_foolhardy_Remacri or 4x-UltraSharp. Put it into the \models\ESRGAN, restart and select it in your hires fix upscaler. download: https://upscale.wiki/wiki/Model_Database

items.name: The Old Shadow run Styles 1990s
items.description:
Envisioning a dystopian cyberpunk future ruled by a fusion of man and machine, dreaming up how such a world would look and feel. Back in the late 1980s and early 90s, an exciting new world opened up with RPG's like Shadowrun. Those books' imagery took the reader into a dystopian future by illustrating the cyberpunk world with high contrast, messy and partially disturbing black-and-white ink images. This unique style was used by various artists during that time, just before the advent of computer-aided drawing tools. This model is trained on imagery and drawing techniques employed during that period.

This updated version has more high-resolution 1k training images and more iterations. Of The Old Shadow run Styles 80s to 90s

Employed in the right way, the model will generate convincing analogue-looking artwork that appears like it has been drawn with ink and pencil using crosshatching and some differing shading technique like using a copy machine. That allows turning pencil greyscale shading into dithering.

The triggering keyword is:

TheOldShadowrunStyles

the list of concepts link

1.1 - update now is also LORA version available

items.name: Corneo's Makima (Chainsaw Man) TI Embedding
items.description:
This is a textual inversion embedding for Makima from Chainsaw Man. Chainsaw Man is an incredible series that you should try out if you haven't already.

Recommended with slight_smile or bored to really get that classic Makima expression. Oh and the clothing was excluded from training so you probably want something like white shirt, collared shirt, black necktie, black pants in the prompt to get the right uniform as shown.

As usual the eyes didn't turn out quite as good as I was hoping for despite focusing on them really heavily, so I also recommend using ringed_eyes in your prompts to try and improve on what this embed does by itself.

Example images created using my 7th Heaven mix https://civitai.com/models/4669/corneos-7th-heaven-mix

Check out my other civitai models for more characters and sex positions! https://civitai.com/user/Master_Corneo

If you enjoy this embed, I genuinely love seeing your creations with it - you can attach them to a review if you're not aware (but not comments sadly)!

items.name: Mangled Merge
items.description:
Introduction:

Mangled Merge V3 has been a labor of love side project for some time. I finally feel it's strong enough for a new iteration. It is great with 2D anime style AND realistic images. It also brings a lot of style with it.

Usage:
Mangled Merge V3 has a custom VAE built in to control contrast and brightness in order to handle both 2D and realistic styles. It is strongly recommended to keep the VAE set to automatic. As far as CFG settings, 7 is the sweet spot, but you can explore between 4 and 10. Self Attention Guidance is recommended, but on a scale between .1 and .3. Anything more can give it too much detail.

Hands and faces can still be an issue from far distances. I suggest adding [:highly detailed face, highly detailed eyes, highly detailed hands:.20] to help alleviate this. This model does much better with high res fix. Odd resolutions MAY give it some trouble without having it enabled.











Mangled Merge V2 is a merge of CharHelper Fine Tuned + Illuminati + RealismEngine. All keywords from CharHelper will work to help guide the model but are not needed.

Note: this model does not contain any nudity to my knowledge however, there are monsters and creepy critters.

nfixer is nice too, but also not needed. CFG scale also plays nicely at 7 and above.

Use Auto for the vae in settings. If you are using a vae based on a SDv1.5 model, you may not get the best results.

Have fun!

Source Models:
CharHelper Fine Tuned
Illuminati Diffusion V1.1
Realism Engine 1.0

Credits to:
Razzz
IlluminatiAI

--------------------------------------------------------------------

Introduction:
Mangled Merge V1 is a merge of 11 different v2.x 768x768 models currently available. All keywords from these models will work to help guide the model but not as powerfully as the individual models they were merged from. However, this is counterbalanced by the amazing versatiliy the v2.1 model gains from merging them all together. Mangled Merge makes for a much improved, much needed general purpose model for anyone interested in using a v2.x model. And there is still room for improvement!

Merged models include:
Redshift, synthetic cmodel, conceptSheet_conceptSheetAlpha, CharHelperV4, classicNegative1521_classicNegative768px, clayitization-SD2.1-768px, cuteRichstyle21_cuteRichstyle, oldjourney_oldjourneyLite, primevalNovaV2_primevalNovaV2, vectorArt_pulpVectorBeta, and vectorArt_vectorArtBeta.

All of the models merged together in Mangled Merge are all absolutely great on their own as well so try theirs out be sure to give them a like! All of their keywords have some effects on Mangled Merge but are somewhat toned down in comparison. If you want the keywords, you can find them on their model sheets.

Use Auto for the vae in settings. If you are using a vae based on a SDv1.5 model, you may not get the best results.


File Name is Mangled_Merge_V1.safetensors. Make sure to download the yaml file along with it or else it won't load for you.

Keywords:
cmodel, clayitization, cbzbb, Oldjourney, classicnegative, concept-art, redshift style, by vector-art, pulp-diffusion, CHV3CZombie, CHV3CAlien, CHV3CBird, CHV3CKnight, CHV3CWizard, CHV3CBarb, CHV3MTroll, CHV3MDeath, CHV3CRogue, CHV3CCyberpunk, CHV3CSamurai, CHV3CRobot, CHV3SLighthouse, CHV3SCute, CHV3SMacro, CHV3SWorld, CHV3SSciFi, CHV3MDragon, CHV3CVehicle,

Source Models:

Redshift (Cinema4D-redshift-render style) keywords = "redshift style"

synthetic-cmodel = comodel2 (glossy/cartoony humanoids, "studio-light" seems implied) keyword="cmodel"

concept-sheet (book-ilustrations, can do dragons quite well, except for overall anatomy) keywords="concept-art"

charhelper (individual-specific) keywords= too many keywords to list HERE, highly specific

classic Negative (photography-style of dreambooth-set) keywords="classicnegative"

jaks-clayitization-image-pack (claymation) , keywords="clayitization"

cute Richstyle (high-contrast BOBBLE-HEADED people/animals , cg-stilized-anatomy mostly) keywords=" cbzbb, cbzbb style, cbzbb style of _____ "

oldjourney ( Midjourney 3 using Dreambooth) keyword="Oldjourney"

primeval Nova (abstract art, bad for realism)

vector-art + VectorPulpBeta (lots of contour-lines, not necessarily cell-shaded, FLASH-cartoon styles and icons) keyword="by vector-art"

Credits to hobolyra, Nitrosocke, jinofcoolnes, pmejna, BudFactory, plasm0, RICHVIP, and starwingdigital for making awesome models to merge with and for allowing their models to be merged and shared. Also to stablediffusioner for putting most of this info sheet together.

items.name: Pastel-Mix [Stylized Anime Model]
items.description:
Huggingface repository goes here.

Interested in supporting me? Buy me a coffee.

A stylized anime model. This model is made with the thought of imitating pastel-like art while introducing the potential of merging LORAs into a model altogether to create a fantastic mix.

Guide

For the settings or parameters, I recommend using these settings.

Sampler: DPM++ 2M Karras

Steps: 20

CFG Scale: 7

Hires. Fix: On

Upscaler: Latent (MUST!)

Hires Steps: 20

Denoising Strength: 0.

I prefer using 0.6 since it's the sweet spot of this model. If you can find a better setting for this model, then good for you lol.

Latent upscaler is the best setting for me since it retains or enhances the pastel style. Other upscalers like Lanczos or Anime6B tends to smoothen them out, removing the pastel-like brushwork.

Please use the VAE that I uploaded in this repository. It is from the Waifu Diffusion team. Credits to haru for letting me rename and upload it.

Tip (Optional)

Putting mksks style in the beginning of the prompt can further influence the pastel-like style and make the output better. It is optional though, so it's up to you. You don't really need it.

Recipe for the mix can be found inside the HF repository.

items.name: Cornflower - Stylized Anime and Hentai Model
items.description:
Cornflower is a comprehensive painting model based on StableDiffusion, trained with specific styles of illustration and merged with multiple models, which is theoretically somewhat different from real-life human painters.

Since the Cornflower model contains multiple files, you need to place all the files in the appropriate locations.

How to use?

The Cornflower model consists of three parts: Checkpoint, Hypernetwork, and Embedding.

Starting with v8, Hypernetwork and Embedding files for the current version will be given in the release notes as a direct link.

You need to put the three files in the corresponding locations and enable them after the installation is complete.

The following parameters are recommended, and the recommended sampler for the current release is DPM++ 3M SDE Exponential.

Steps: 20+ (12+ for preview)

Sampler: DPM++ 3M SDE Exponential

CFG scale: 7

Size: 512x768 + Hires

Clip skip: 2

e.g. prompt

art by Cornflower, dreamy, full body

(1girl, (long golden wavy hair),(red and white frilled bikini:1.2),(the girl is floating in the water),(seaweeds,fish,sunlight),shiny eyes,beautiful detailed eyes,elegant eyelashes,beautiful detailed face,(an extremely delicate and beautiful) , studio photography, extremely detailed wallpaper ,hair hangs down to the shoulder, eyes visible through hair ,eyelashes covered by hair,(small breasts))

Negative prompt: (worst quality, low quality:1.4) ,lowres,bad anatomy,bad hands, text, error, missing fingers,extra digit, fewer digits, cropped, worstquality, low quality, normal quality,jpegartifacts,signature, watermark, username,blurry,bad feet,cropped,poorly drawn hands,poorly drawn face,mutation,deformed,worst quality,low quality,normal quality,jpeg artifacts,signature,watermark,extra fingers,fewer digits,extra limbs,extra arms,extra legs,malformed limbs,fused fingers,too many fingers,long neck,mutated hands,polar lowres,bad body,bad proportions,gross proportions,text,error,missing fingers,missing arms,missing legs,extra digit, ((Intricate clothes, too much lace, too much dacoration on clothes, ))

Please download both the Hypernetwork file and the Embedding file for this version.

DPM++ SDE Karras is recommended.

Changelog:

  • The v9 version brings the overall style closer to the classic v4 version through multiple merge operations.

  • Specifically, firstly, the v8 base model and the ChilloutMix model are merged with the COSINE method, and then the results are merged with the v8 base model and the PastelMix model at a ratio of 0.3, the results are merged with the PastelMix model with a custom method close to normal distribution, and finally the results are merged with the 9527 model by the OrangeMix-like method to obtain the v9 base model.

modelVersions.name: v8

Please download both the Hypernetwork file and the Embedding file for this version.

DPM++ SDE Karras is recommended.

Changelog:

  • The v8 version greatly strengthens the painting style of the model through multiple merging operations, and fixes the logical relationship problem of the v7 model to a certain extent.

  • Specifically, the v6 checkpoint and the pastelMix model were first merged using the TRUE_CUBIC method, and then the results were merged with the dalcefoV3Painting model and the Counterfeit-V2.0 model at a scale of 0.2, the results were copied, the copy was merged with the BasilMix model according to the Abyss2 method, and finally the two models were blockmerged to obtain the v8 checkpoint.

items.name: optionalAI (Style embedding)
items.description:
This is a more artistic style embedding, that is inspired by the work of OptionalTypo. It's a rather simplistic Anime style inversion, but with a colorful twist in most parts.

Also check out my other embeddings here.

Trained on waifu-diffusion-v1-3-float32.ckpt, but works best when used in connection with DreamShaper 3.3 or Protogen 3.3 (Anime). Others may give you different results, but nevertheless it's sometimes very refreshing what comes out of the process.

I usually used Anything-V3.0 VAE - or vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned works fine, too. I also use the negative embedding named Deep Negative from time to time. So take a good look into my examples for that. And yes, it's also compatible with lewd stuff.

The keyword is the filename (without the .pt) you put into your embeddings folder (usually optional_styleAI).

items.name: Aslan's Sci Fi
items.description:
These embeddings are trained on classic Sci-fi action movies from the 70s to the 2000s. I ultimately wanted something that could combine the classic scifi aesthetic and the realism of live action cinematography.

--------

To use these embeddings in AUTOMATIC1111, copy them to your embeddings folder in your stable-diffusion-webui directory. No need to restart, just invoke the embedding from your prompt. Make sure you are using a compatible model or you will get errors!

--------

The Sci-fi embeddings were all trained on 465 768x768 images that were cropped and tagged using BLIP for training.
--------

Like most other 2.1 textual inversions this works best when paired up with other embeddings and good negative prompting.

This LoRA generates images based on the style of Itaru Hinoue's artwork for Tactics/Key's 2000s-era visual novels, specifically MOON.

This LoRA is fantastic for getting a 90s or early 2000s aesthetic into images. You can control the strength and merge it with other models to get the perfect mix of styles.

There are no specific tags to invoke the style, like my other LoRAs. However, this includes tagging to invoke specific characters.

amasawa ikumi, amasawa ikumi (track), amasawa ikumi (young), amasawa miyako, kanuma youko, kanuma youko (pajamas), kanuma youko (young), mima haruka, mima ryousuke, nakura yui, nakura yuri, shounen, shounen (school uniform), takatsuki

items.description:
PLEASE NOTE: This is my first model I have ever created. I used the Merge Block Weighted extension for AUTOMATIC1111 to bring together Dreamlike PhotoReal 2.0 and LarryAIDraw/baka_gape_nainsfw_10. After a great deal of trial and error I settled on using the SMOOTHSTEP^2 preset.

This model focuses specifically on huge dildo insertions. It was intended for all kinds of insertions and gaping but so far it works best on dildos.

The model responds reasonably well to Danbooru tags, and responds very well to the tags listed.

You can get other poses if you work the prompt hard enough, but the phrase "squatting on a huge dildo" will get immediate results.

The use of vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned.vae.pt and the negative models bad_prompt_version2, and bad-hands-5, are highly recommended.

The model combines well with most textual embeddings.

Recommended settings

Sampling Steps: 20-25

Sampling method: Euler a

Restore faces: on

Highres fix: on

CFG Scale: 7 for txt2img and 15 for img2img

Dreamlike PhotoReal uses a modified CreativeML OpenRAIL-M license. Please be sure to read and comply with it.

https://civitai.com/models/3811/dreamlike-photoreal-20

items.name: Murata Yusuke (One Punch Man) Style LoRA
items.description:
Murata Yuusuke (One-Punch Man) style LoRA

Making models can be expensive. Do you like what I do? Consider supporting me on Patreon üÖøÔ∏è or feel free to buy me a coffee ‚òï

Another great mangaka. This LoRA can do colored artworks or b&w stuff and can imitate Murata's style pretty well. I've tested it on some models, but Anything V4.5 seems to be the one that works best here, as it has less of a defined style. Weight is usually around 0.6, but the ideal one can vary between 0.2 and 0.7 (yes, even 0.2, this can be quite strong sometimes). Triggers with murata yuusuke but it's optional.

NOTE: this is not a character LoRA. The fact that it can imitate some OPM characters is collateral, but this is very much a style model. If you want OPM characters you'll have to describe them as shown in the examples and you also need a bit of luck.

Thanks to Aojiru on Discord for helping me test the model and prepare the Example images.

How to use LoRA's in auto1111:

  • Update webui (use git pull like here or redownload it)

  • Copy the file to stable-diffusion-webui/models/lora

  • Select your LoRA like in this video

  • Make sure to change the weight (by default it's :1 which is usually too high)

items.name: Saoirse Ronan Embedding
items.description:
Saoirse Ronan embedding created by Airathias

Usage of a VAE highly advised, it likes to make the pupils huge and blobby. Embedding was created in 800 steps, and a large number of vectors per token so keep your prompt short and concise. I've only seen weird results with long prompts, and anything very anime-ish. Anything resembling realism will render just fine.

I added prompts to a few of the example images, should work fine. These prompts were basically blatantly copied from other examples throughout the website. If I copied yours, mea culpa. You can use this without crediting me.

The embedding was trained on stock SD 1.5, so it should work for many if not most models based off of 1.5.

Images listed are made using a handful of models to test, including:

  • Stock SD 1.5

  • DreamShaper (https://civitai.com/models/4384/dreamshaper) (amazing results, some of the best ones were made with this)

  • UberRealistic Dreamy PFG Porn (https://civitai.com/models/3751/uberrealistic-dreamy-pfg-porn)

  • Babes (https://civitai.com/models/2220/babes)
